 {"id":"franken_numpy-ifd0","title":"Match NaN-coefficient parity in NxN solve/inv","description":"`solve_nxn`/`inv_nxn` now allow infinity-containing matrices and non-finite RHS, but NaN-bearing NxN coefficient matrices still collapse to all-NaN outputs where NumPy preserves some finite substructure.\n\nEvidence:\n- `np.linalg.solve([[nan,1,0],[0,3,1],[2,0,3]], [1,2,3]) -> [nan, 0.45454545, 0.63636364]`\n- current Rust path returns broader NaN contamination.\n\nGoal: close the remaining NaN-matrix parity gap without regressing det/slogdet or singular finite behavior.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:51:09.145395843Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T18:34:00.532108764Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T18:34:00.531842710Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
